Rototiller on top of Beds for destroying sugarcane stubble.  Any growing crop or weeds are killed. About 60% of the surface is disturbed.  About half of the bed height is flattened leaving a ridge height of about 6 inches.  082107 DTL

Rototiller for weed control in row middles of growing crop.  Current crop is not killed.  Incidental residue from weeds or growing cover is added by the "add other cover" process.  When this operation is used in a management record, the user must enter the residue type and amount.  043008 DTL
Rototiller for weed control in row middles of growing crop.  Crop is not killed. 11-30-01 DTL

Sand fighter on beds.  Makes roughened surface with spade points mounted on spiderwheels mounted on a shaft.  Similar to a rotary hoe except spade points are further apart and not pointed.  Also similar to a mulch treader but not as aggressive and not operated on a skew.  02-22-2016 LOS

Reciprocating spader used as a full width primary tillage operation in growing weeds or cover, residue or previously tilled soil..  Speed is artifically set higher than actual ground speed  to account for the mixing action of the PTO driven spades.  Soil Disturbance is high similar to that of a roto tiller but the machine action is more like that of hand spading whereby the soil is lifted and fractured.  If used to till under weeds or growing cover, the management record needs to have initiated the cover or weed growth prior to use of this operation.  06-24-10 DTL
Adjusted speed and tillage type to be more agressive than rototiller since the operating depth of this implement is twice that of the rototiller. 03292022 GGF

Reciprocating spader used as a full width primary tillage operation in growing weeds or cover, residue or previously tilled soil..  Speed is artifically set higher than actual ground speed  to account for the mixing action of the PTO driven spades.  Soil Disturbance is high similar to that of a roto tiller but the machine action is more like that of hand spading whereby the soil is lifted and fractured.  If used to till under weeds or growing cover, the management record needs to have initiated the cover or weed growth prior to use of this operation.  06-24-10 DTL
Adjusted speed and tillage type to be slightly less aggressive than rototiller at similar depth 03292022 GGF

Rolling Stalk Chopper, ground driven with double rotor gangs covering the full width of the machine.  This record represents operation on unridged ground where the weight of the machine is distriibuted across 100% of the working width. 110906 DTL
Adjusted speed and tillage type to be less agressive than rototiller and spader.  Changed residue burial ratio and resurfacing according to 2022 protocol. 03292022 GGF

Rolling Stalk Chopper, light weight frame pull type, ground driven with single rotor gang covering the full width of the machine on flat planted ground.  This operation represents about 30% surface disturbance.  Would represent light machine operating on heavy residue condition from high yielding s,mall grain or corn.   111510 DTL
Adjusted speed and tillage type to be less agressive than rototiller, spader and Stalk chopper, rolling.  Changed residue burial ratio and resurfacing according to 2022 protocol. 03312022 GGF

A pair of concave disk blades mounted in a Vee configuration and spaced to pinch and pull stalk and root ball.    Approximately 60 % of the surface left  undisturbed.   11/15/06 DTL

A pair of concave disk blades mounted in a Vee configuration and spaced to pinch and pull cotton or corn stalks and root ball and lay the stubble flat.   Approximately 35 -40% of the surface left  undisturbed.   11/15/06 DTL DTL
Adusted Rec. till. depth to 2.5 inches from 3 inches and reduced Rec. speed to 7 mph.  Changed residue burial ratio and resurfacing according to 2022 protocol. 04112022 GGF

Stalk slicer.  A pair of flat disk blades mounted in a Vee configuration and spaced to run directly on the previous crop row to cut the stalk and root ball and also lightly till a zone into which the next crop is no-tilled or striptilled. Undercutter sweeps.  Also known as blade plows or Noble blades 24" to 40" wide.  Run shallow to undercut stubble and weeds, thus killing weeds but leaving stubble upright.12-18-01 DTL

Operation: Sweep plow wider  than 40 in w/ mulch treader
Description: Stubble Mulch undercutter or blade plow, Sweeps or V-blades 30+" wide with a mulch treader attachment . Run shallow to undercut stubble and weeds.  The mulch treader attachment flattens, and anchors the straw and exposes the roots. 11/08/01  DTL REV 110207 DTL

This is a secondary operation to bedding.  The beds are undercut 100% disturbance, but the surface maintains some crusting (larger clods) over 60% of the bed.  The furrow is tilled with a shovel about 40% of the surface.  Beds are not build back.  The existing ridges (ht & width) are used.  Cloned ARS Bedder operation.  RUSLE, Sweep Plow.  MAS 1-22-07
Stubble Mulch undercutter or blade plow, Sweeps or V-blades 40+" wide. Run shallow to undercut stubble and weeds, thus killing weeds but leaving stubble upright.  12-18-01 DTL

Single low crown cultivator sweep run on each row to undercut and kill crops such as cotton.  Run 4 to 6 inches deep under each row lifting and fracturing a zone about a foot wide on 38 to 40 inch centers. Very little disturbance of existing surface residue cover.  062304 DTL

Operation: Sweep, single under row, regrow perennial
Description: Single low crown cultivator sweep run on each row to undercut and kill the above ground growth of crops such as Artichoke or Asparagus  and stimulate new growth from the roots or crowns.  Run 1 to 2  inches deep under each row lifting and fracturing a zone about a foot wide on 38 to 40 inch centers. Very little disturbance of existing surface residue cover.  041608 DTL
Tree spade used to dig nursery stock. Assumes bare soil condition and holes left open.  071403 DTL

Tree spade used to dig nursery stock.  Assumes trees in sod or cover crop cover and holes plugged with plug from tree planting site.  Regrowth file requested should be permanent cover not harvested.  071403 DTL
